This paper is about few-shot learning for image classification, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses meta-learning, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) that focuses on learning to learn. Additionally, the paper uses unsupervised learning, which is a common technique in natural language processing (cs.CL) and neural networks (cs.NE). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.LG and cs.CV, followed by cs.AI, cs.CL, and cs.NE.
